Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

While it boils, pop a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the @Tikka Masala Paste{75%g}, @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Creme Fraiche{75%g}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water{150%ml} (see pantry for both). Stir to combine and bring to the boil.

Next, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, stir the @Diced British Chicken Breast{260%g} into the frying pan. Bring to the boil and lower the heat.

Simmer, ~{10-12%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Once the rice is cooked, drain, pop back in the #pan{} and cover.

When the chicken is cooked, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} in handfuls so it's piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Stir in the @Butter{20%g} (see pantry) until melted.

Share the rice and curry between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!